results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows: the number of hydrocarbon structures that can be drawn with a given number of carbons and units of unsaturation.
comment: Computed over a period of several years and confirmed using the Molgen program.
link: David Consiglio, Jr., Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..130
example: a(3,1) = 2 because there are two structures that contain 3 carbons and have 1 unit of unsaturation (propene and cyclopropane).
results.author: _David Consiglio, Jr._, Jan 28 2008, Apr 23 2008
